element.documentation:
The ability to manage requirements through the lifecycle of a service. It collects, refines, scopes, and tracks progress of and maintains requirements before and after an IT Initiative(s) ha(s)(ve) been delivered. It maintains the traceability of each requirement to the original source (demand, IT or business standard or policy, and/or requestor) and to the source (code), solutions and/or test cases throughout the service lifecycle. Requirements can be maintained for different levels. For example:
- At an enterprise level, external market business and IT requirements are maintained;
- At a tactical or service automation level, software process and service automation requirements are managed;
- At an operational level, performance and availability requirements are managed.
